1
00:00:03,220 --> 00:00:05,353
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

2
00:00:17,104 --> 00:00:19,541
Pastor Drew: GOD HAS
A PECULIAR WAY OF TESTING YOU

3
00:00:19,584 --> 00:00:21,499
WHEN YOU LEAST EXPECT IT.

4
00:00:21,543 --> 00:00:23,806
[ DOG BARKING ]

5
00:00:23,849 --> 00:00:26,069
WHEN I ARRIVED IN HAVERILL,

6
00:00:26,113 --> 00:00:28,419
A SMALL TOWN IN THE GREEN HILLS OF VERMONT,

7
00:00:28,463 --> 00:00:30,726
THE CHURCH WAS DECLINING
AND IN DESPERATE NEED OF HELP.

8
00:00:37,515 --> 00:00:39,909
I HAD PRAYED FOR AN OPPORTUNITY TO GET OUT OF NEW YORK,

9
00:00:39,952 --> 00:00:43,391
WHERE I WAS JUST ANOTHER FACE
IN A CROWD...

10
00:00:43,434 --> 00:00:44,957
STEP INTO A COMMUNITY

11
00:00:45,001 --> 00:00:47,308
THAT NEEDED A RESURGENCE
OF FAITH AND IDENTITY...

12
00:00:49,875 --> 00:00:51,529
...WHERE I COULD MAKE
A REAL DIFFERENCE.

13
00:00:55,664 --> 00:00:58,971
I'VE ALWAYS FELT THAT CHANGE
COMES FROM A GRASSROOTS EFFORT

14
00:00:59,015 --> 00:01:02,801
AND THAT A CONGREGATION GROWS
WITH THE YOUNGER GENERATION.

15
00:01:05,152 --> 00:01:08,677
SO I STARTED A MUSICAL YOUTH
GROUP CALLED THE SERMONS.

16
00:01:08,720 --> 00:01:12,594
WE'D PRACTICE A COUPLE TIMES
A WEEK AND PERFORM REGULARLY

17
00:01:12,637 --> 00:01:14,857
FOR THE TOURISTS WHO VISIT
FOR THE OVERPRICED ANTIQUES,

18
00:01:14,900 --> 00:01:17,207
ICE CREAM, AND MAPLE SYRUP.

19
00:01:23,735 --> 00:01:25,389
DURING THE SUNDAY SERVICES,

20
00:01:25,433 --> 00:01:27,739
CONCERNS STILL
OUTNUMBER THE JOYS,

21
00:01:27,783 --> 00:01:29,567
AND SOMETIMES
I WISH MY CONGREGANTS

22
00:01:29,611 --> 00:01:32,048
WOULD TAKE A LITTLE PROZAC
WITH THEIR PRAYER.

23
00:01:32,092 --> 00:01:34,442
THE DOWNSIDE TO LIFE
IN A SMALL TOWN

24
00:01:34,485 --> 00:01:37,488
IS EVERYONE WANTS TO KNOW
EACH OTHER'S BUSINESS.

25
00:01:37,532 --> 00:01:41,362
SECRETS BEHIND CLOSED DOORS
ARE EVENTUALLY EXPOSED.

26
00:01:41,405 --> 00:01:43,929
TAKE THE HAYWARDS.

27
00:01:43,973 --> 00:01:46,106
THEY APPEARED TO HAVE IT ALL...

28
00:01:49,326 --> 00:01:51,111
THE ALL-AMERICAN FAMILY...

29
00:01:54,418 --> 00:01:56,072
...BLESSED WITH GOOD HEALTH

30
00:01:56,116 --> 00:01:58,944
AND A BEAUTIFUL DAUGHTER,
KATIE.

31
00:01:58,988 --> 00:02:01,730
SHE WAS EVERY PARENT'S DREAM...

32
00:02:04,776 --> 00:02:07,649
...KIND-HEARTED, RESPONSIBLE,
AND SMART.

33
00:02:13,611 --> 00:02:15,961
GEORGE OWNED A SUCCESSFUL CHAIN OF SPORTING-GOOD STORES

34
00:02:16,005 --> 00:02:19,922
ACROSS THE STATE...
EVERY WOMAN'S DREAM.

35
00:02:19,965 --> 00:02:22,011
ALICE WAS A HOMEMAKER,

36
00:02:22,054 --> 00:02:25,145
AND SHE WAS ACTIVE IN OUR
CHURCH, LOYAL AND STRONG.

37
00:02:38,810 --> 00:02:41,509
THAT'S THE TROUBLE WITH BEING
ON THE OUTSIDE, LOOKING IN...

38
00:02:41,552 --> 00:02:42,901
YOU NEVER REALLY KNOW.

39
00:02:42,945 --> 00:02:45,034
[ GUNSHOT ]

40
00:02:45,077 --> 00:02:50,170
[ CAMERA SHUTTER CLICKING ]

41
00:02:52,955 --> 00:02:55,566
[ POLICE RADIO CHATTER ]

42
00:02:55,610 --> 00:02:58,656
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

43
00:02:58,700 --> 00:03:00,658
OH, HEY, EMMET.

44
00:03:00,702 --> 00:03:01,833
HI, CATHERINE.

45
00:03:01,877 --> 00:03:03,357
WHAT DO WE GOT?

46
00:03:03,400 --> 00:03:05,794
GEORGE HAYWARD STRANGLED
HIS WIFE, ALICE,

47
00:03:05,837 --> 00:03:07,361
AND THEN SHOT HIMSELF.

48
00:03:07,404 --> 00:03:09,493
OH, MY GOD.

49
00:03:09,537 --> 00:03:11,452
I DON'T THINK I'VE EVER SEEN YOU
LOOK SHOCKED BEFORE.

50
00:03:11,495 --> 00:03:13,062
THEY SEEMED LIKE
THE PERFECT COUPLE,

51
00:03:13,105 --> 00:03:16,761
LIKE, UH,
REAL NORMAN ROCKWELL STUFF.

52
00:03:16,805 --> 00:03:17,893
DANCE STARTS
IN THE DINING ROOM,

53
00:03:17,936 --> 00:03:19,721
AND IT ENDS RIGHT HERE.

54
00:03:19,764 --> 00:03:21,853
LOOKS LIKE SHE PUT UP QUITE
A FIGHT ALONG THE WAY...

55
00:03:21,897 --> 00:03:24,116
A LOT OF BLOODY SKIN
UNDER HER FINGERNAILS

56
00:03:24,160 --> 00:03:25,770
APPEAR TO MATCH
MARKS ON HIM...

57
00:03:25,814 --> 00:03:27,598
WHAT'S LEFT OF HIM.

58
00:03:27,642 --> 00:03:28,860
THEIR DAUGHTER...
WHERE'S KATIE?
HAS SHE BEEN BY HERE?

59
00:03:28,904 --> 00:03:30,906
SPENT THE NIGHT
AT A FRIEND'S HOUSE... TINA.

60
00:03:30,949 --> 00:03:32,560
TINA'S MOTHER, GINNY,

61
00:03:32,603 --> 00:03:34,214
IS THE ONE WHO ACTUALLY FOUND
THE BODIES.

62
00:03:34,257 --> 00:03:36,216
ALICE WAS APPARENTLY LATE
FOR SOME CHURCH THING,

63
00:03:36,259 --> 00:03:39,001
SO GINNY CALLS, NO ANSWER,
COMES TO CHECK ON HER.

64
00:03:39,044 --> 00:03:41,743
IT SEEMS MR. HAYWARD
WAS QUITE A DRINKER...

65
00:03:41,786 --> 00:03:43,527
BEER BOTTLES EVERYWHERE.

66
00:03:43,571 --> 00:03:46,400
PLACE SMELLS LIKE A FRAT HOUSE
ON A SUNDAY MORNING.

67
00:03:46,443 --> 00:03:49,359
HOW'S THAT FIT INTO YOUR
NORMAN ROCKWELL PICTURE?

68
00:03:49,403 --> 00:03:51,927
IT DOESN'T.

69
00:03:51,970 --> 00:03:53,711
WHAT HAPPENED TO YOUR HAND?

70
00:03:53,755 --> 00:03:56,192
THE DOG BIT ME.

71
00:03:56,236 --> 00:03:57,889
WELL, DID YOU CALL
ANIMAL CONTROL?

72
00:03:57,933 --> 00:04:01,502
NO. I DIDN'T HAVE TO.
PASTOR SHOWED UP.

73
00:04:01,545 --> 00:04:02,720
[ DOG BARKING ]

74
00:04:02,764 --> 00:04:03,982
WHOA. WATCH IT.

75
00:04:04,026 --> 00:04:06,115
DOG DOESN'T SEEM
TO MIND HIM.

76
00:04:06,158 --> 00:04:07,508
MM.

77
00:04:07,551 --> 00:04:08,987
DISPATCHER: Stand by.

78
00:04:09,031 --> 00:04:10,728
Man: DISPATCH,
THIS IS BURNHAM 23,

79
00:04:10,772 --> 00:04:12,556
LEAVING THE SCENE
IN MAYBE 10 MINUTES.

80
00:04:12,600 --> 00:04:13,992
Stand by.

81
00:04:14,036 --> 00:04:17,474
[ BARKING CONTINUES ]

82
00:04:17,518 --> 00:04:19,128
WATCH THAT DOG, GUYS.

83
00:04:19,171 --> 00:04:20,869
CATHERINE.
PASTOR.

84
00:04:20,912 --> 00:04:21,957
GINNY CALLED, HYSTERICAL.

85
00:04:22,000 --> 00:04:23,741
I THOUGHT I'D COME BY

86
00:04:23,785 --> 00:04:25,265
AND SEE IF THERE'S ANYTHING
I COULD DO TO HELP.

87
00:04:25,308 --> 00:04:26,440
HOW ABOUT GETTING THAT DOG
OUT OF HERE?

88
00:04:26,483 --> 00:04:27,745
NAH, WE'RE GOOD.

89
00:04:27,789 --> 00:04:30,400
ALL RIGHT, I'LL TAKE HER
BACK TO KATIE.

90
00:04:30,444 --> 00:04:31,880
THANKS, PASTOR.
WE APPRECIATE IT.

91
00:04:33,838 --> 00:04:36,014
NEWS TRAVELS FAST.

92
00:04:36,058 --> 00:04:39,104
WELL, SMALL TOWN.
LET'S GO.

93
00:04:39,148 --> 00:04:42,020
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

94
00:04:55,817 --> 00:04:58,123
Man: OH, I'M SO GLAD
YOU COULD BE HERE FOR ALICE.

95
00:04:58,167 --> 00:04:59,995
THANK YOU.

96
00:05:00,038 --> 00:05:01,779
[ INDISTINCT SPEAKING ]

97
00:05:01,823 --> 00:05:03,868
GOD BLESS YOU.

98
00:05:03,912 --> 00:05:06,175
HELLO, MR. JOHNSON.

99
00:05:06,218 --> 00:05:08,133
THANK YOU GUYS FOR COMING.

100
00:05:08,177 --> 00:05:09,700
THANK YOU.

101
00:05:09,744 --> 00:05:12,834
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

102
00:05:12,877 --> 00:05:14,401
NOW, KATIE, YOU SURE

103
00:05:14,444 --> 00:05:17,229
I CAN'T TALK YOU
INTO TAKING THE PLUNGE?

104
00:05:17,273 --> 00:05:19,231
TWO FOR THE PRICE
OF ONE TODAY?

105
00:05:19,275 --> 00:05:20,885
YEAH, I THINK
IT'S JUST MOM TODAY.

106
00:05:20,929 --> 00:05:24,062
ALL RIGHT. I'M GONNA STAY
ON YOU, YOUNG LADY.

107
00:05:24,106 --> 00:05:25,977
THANKS.
[ CHUCKLES ]

108
00:05:26,021 --> 00:05:28,458
HE'S SO EXCITED.

109
00:05:28,502 --> 00:05:30,460
I'M SO GLAD YOU'RE HERE,
SWEETIE.

110
00:05:30,504 --> 00:05:32,332
YEAH, ME, TOO.

111
00:05:35,639 --> 00:05:36,727
READY?

112
00:05:36,771 --> 00:05:38,468
YEAH, I AM.

113
00:05:45,127 --> 00:05:47,434
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

114
00:05:56,747 --> 00:06:00,142
[ SIGHS ]

115
00:06:00,185 --> 00:06:04,059
ALICE HAYWARD, DO YOU BELIEVE
IN THE LORD JESUS CHRIST

116
00:06:04,102 --> 00:06:05,626
AS YOUR PERSONAL SAVIOR?

117
00:06:05,669 --> 00:06:07,584
I DO.

118
00:06:07,628 --> 00:06:08,890
AND DO YOU INTEND

119
00:06:08,933 --> 00:06:11,632
TO FOLLOW HIM ALL THE DAYS
OF YOUR LIFE?

120
00:06:11,675 --> 00:06:12,546
I DO.

121
00:06:16,071 --> 00:06:17,028
[ SIGHS ]

122
00:06:17,072 --> 00:06:19,161
LEAN BACK.

123
00:06:25,950 --> 00:06:27,648
[ LIGHT LAUGHTER ]

124
00:06:37,048 --> 00:06:38,789
THERE.

125
00:06:40,965 --> 00:06:43,881
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

126
00:06:43,925 --> 00:06:45,535
[ SIGHS HEAVILY ]

127
00:06:45,579 --> 00:06:46,841
[ DOG WHIMPERS ]

128
00:06:49,800 --> 00:06:52,194
[ BIRD SQUAWKING ]

129
00:07:07,818 --> 00:07:09,080
HOW IS SHE?

130
00:07:15,130 --> 00:07:16,697
HER DAD JUST CHOKED
HER MOM TO DEATH

131
00:07:16,740 --> 00:07:17,828
AND BLEW HIS HEAD OFF.

132
00:07:17,872 --> 00:07:19,221
HOW DO YOU THINK
SHE'S DOING?

133
00:07:19,264 --> 00:07:20,570
GINNY, WE HAVE TO STICK
TOGETHER FOR KATIE.

134
00:07:20,614 --> 00:07:23,007
HI, PASTOR DREW.

135
00:07:23,051 --> 00:07:25,749
[ EXHALES SHARPLY, SNIFFLES ]

136
00:07:25,793 --> 00:07:26,794
[ CRIES ]

137
00:07:26,837 --> 00:07:28,186
IN.

138
00:07:28,230 --> 00:07:30,537
I'M SO SORRY.

139
00:07:30,580 --> 00:07:32,495
I'M HERE FOR YOU, KATIE.

140
00:07:41,156 --> 00:07:44,333
I'M HERE FOR YOU.

141
00:07:58,956 --> 00:08:02,003
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

142
00:08:02,046 --> 00:08:04,919
WE SHARED SOMETHING
DEEPLY PROFOUND TODAY.

143
00:08:04,962 --> 00:08:07,661
I WISH I COULD HUG YOU.

144
00:08:07,704 --> 00:08:09,489
YOU CAN HUG ME, ALICE.

145
00:08:13,797 --> 00:08:15,190
MM.

146
00:08:19,150 --> 00:08:20,761
I'LL GET SOME ICED TEA.

147
00:08:20,804 --> 00:08:22,806
OH!

148
00:08:22,850 --> 00:08:23,981
[ LAUGHTER ]

149
00:08:24,025 --> 00:08:25,983
I AM SO PROUD OF YOU.[ CHUCKLES ]

150
00:08:26,027 --> 00:08:28,203
I KNOW THIS SORT OF THING
ISN'T VERY COOL.

151
00:08:28,246 --> 00:08:30,161
NO, IT'S COOL IF YOU DO IT.

152
00:08:30,205 --> 00:08:32,860
YOU KNOW WHAT ELSE
IS REALLY COOL?

153
00:08:32,903 --> 00:08:34,557
THE FRAY.

154
00:08:34,601 --> 00:08:37,212
AND, UH, THEY'RE GIVING
A CONCERT TONIGHT IN ALBANY.

155
00:08:37,255 --> 00:08:38,692
WOW.

156
00:08:38,735 --> 00:08:40,650
AND I WON TWO TICKETS.

157
00:08:40,694 --> 00:08:42,347
THAT IS GREAT.

158
00:08:42,391 --> 00:08:44,393
YOU'RE IN ON THIS.

159
00:08:44,436 --> 00:08:46,961
I THOUGHT KATIE COULD STAY
WITH US AFTERWARD.

160
00:08:47,004 --> 00:08:49,833
YOU HAD A BIG DAY.
YOU DESERVE SOME PEACE.

161
00:08:49,877 --> 00:08:51,269
PLEASE?

162
00:08:53,489 --> 00:08:55,186
DID YOU WANT TO CHECK
WITH DAD?

163
00:08:55,230 --> 00:08:57,362
OH, WHY?
I KNOW HE'D SAY YES.

164
00:08:57,406 --> 00:08:59,147
NO. GO. HAVE FUN.

165
00:08:59,190 --> 00:09:00,148
REALLY?
[ LAUGHS ]

166
00:09:00,191 --> 00:09:02,150
THANK YOU. THANK YOU.

167
00:09:02,193 --> 00:09:05,066
BUT NO DRINKING,
NO SMOKING.
NOPE.

168
00:09:05,109 --> 00:09:07,285
AND GET ME A T-SHIRT.
I LOVE THE FRAY.

169
00:09:07,329 --> 00:09:09,549
YOU'RE THE COOLEST MOM EVER.

170
00:09:09,592 --> 00:09:11,028
I'LL BE CAREFUL
WHEN I DRIVE, OKAY?
OKAY.

171
00:09:11,072 --> 00:09:12,377
ARE YOU SURE YOU'LL BE OKAY
TONIGHT?

172
00:09:12,421 --> 00:09:14,162
YEAH, OF COURSE.
HAVE FUN.

173
00:09:14,205 --> 00:09:15,990
Woman: HI, HEATHER.
NICE TO SEE YOU.

174
00:09:16,991 --> 00:09:19,123
YOU DID IT.

175
00:09:19,167 --> 00:09:21,256
NO ONE CAN TAKE THIS
AWAY FROM YOU.

176
00:09:23,127 --> 00:09:24,607
LET'S TALK LATER.

177
00:09:24,651 --> 00:09:27,262
STOP BY NEXT TIME
YOU'RE SHOPPING.
OKAY.

178
00:09:27,305 --> 00:09:31,179
[ CONVERSATIONS CONTINUE ]

179
00:09:31,222 --> 00:09:34,399
ALICE.
HEATHER. YOU CAME.
[ CHUCKLES ]

180
00:09:34,443 --> 00:09:36,445
I DIDN'T WANT TO MISS
THIS SPECIAL MOMENT FOR YOU.

181
00:09:36,488 --> 00:09:37,794
I STAYED IN THE BACK.

182
00:09:37,838 --> 00:09:39,317
I DIDN'T WANT
TO DRAW ATTENTION.

183
00:09:39,361 --> 00:09:42,059
THIS IS FOR YOU...
A GANESH,

184
00:09:42,103 --> 00:09:44,409
TO HELP REMOVE ALL OBSTACLES
FROM YOUR PATH.

185
00:09:44,453 --> 00:09:47,935
IT'S BEAUTIFUL.
THANK YOU.

186
00:09:47,978 --> 00:09:50,502
HEATHER LaROCHE
CAME TO MY BAPTISM.

187
00:09:50,546 --> 00:09:53,157
YES, I SEE.
HELLO, MISS LaROCHE.

188
00:09:53,201 --> 00:09:54,768
HI.
NICE TO MEET YOU.

189
00:09:54,811 --> 00:09:55,986
WHAT DID YOU THINK?

190
00:09:56,030 --> 00:09:57,901
IMMERSION, INCLUSION.

191
00:09:57,945 --> 00:09:59,990
YOU GOT RID OF THE BIBLE.

192
00:10:00,034 --> 00:10:02,863
COULD HAVE BEEN
A PAGAN RITUAL.

193
00:10:02,906 --> 00:10:04,952
DOES THAT MEAN YOU LIKED IT?

194
00:10:04,995 --> 00:10:08,085
IT MEANS OUR BELIEFS

195
00:10:08,129 --> 00:10:10,218
AREN'T ALWAYS AS FAR APART
AS ONE MIGHT THINK.

196
00:10:12,089 --> 00:10:14,526
IS YOUR HUSBAND HERE?
I WANTED TO MEET HIM.

197
00:10:14,570 --> 00:10:18,052
NO, HE, UM... HE WANTED
TO COME, BUT HE HAD TO WORK.

198
00:10:18,095 --> 00:10:20,097
SO WE'LL HAVE A CELEBRATORY
DINNER TONIGHT.

199
00:10:20,141 --> 00:10:22,317
MORE PIE FOR US, RIGHT? YEAH.

200
00:10:24,972 --> 00:10:28,410
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

201
00:10:28,453 --> 00:10:30,630
[ SILVERWARE CLINKING ]

202
00:10:34,024 --> 00:10:35,983
[ CHUCKLES ]

203
00:10:36,026 --> 00:10:38,159
[ SMOOCHES ]

204
00:10:38,202 --> 00:10:39,987
SO, YOU GOT BAPTIZED TODAY?

205
00:10:40,030 --> 00:10:41,423
MM-HMM.

206
00:10:41,466 --> 00:10:44,774
REALLY?

207
00:10:44,818 --> 00:10:47,124
THOUGHT
WE HAD DISCUSSED IT.

208
00:10:47,168 --> 00:10:49,561
WE DID.

209
00:10:49,605 --> 00:10:51,563
[ Chuckling ]
AND I INVITED YOU.

210
00:10:51,607 --> 00:10:54,001
YOU MUST HAVE
JUST FORGOTTEN.

211
00:10:54,044 --> 00:10:55,742
LET'S EAT.

212
00:11:00,094 --> 00:11:01,443
WHAT,
YOU WENT IN THE RIVER?

213
00:11:01,486 --> 00:11:03,358
YEAH.YOU ACTUALLY GOT
IN THE WATER?

214
00:11:03,401 --> 00:11:05,055
[ Chuckling ]
YEAH.

215
00:11:06,883 --> 00:11:09,146
SO, WHO WAS THERE?

216
00:11:09,190 --> 00:11:14,108
UM... THANKS... THE WOMEN'S
CIRCLE FROM THE CHURCH

217
00:11:14,151 --> 00:11:16,023
AND GINNY, OF COURSE.

218
00:11:16,066 --> 00:11:17,981
OF COURSE.

219
00:11:18,025 --> 00:11:19,200
WHO ELSE?

220
00:11:21,550 --> 00:11:23,247
OH, HEATHER LaROCHE.

221
00:11:23,291 --> 00:11:25,728
[ LAUGHS ] COME ON.

222
00:11:25,772 --> 00:11:28,862
WHAT, THE CRACKPOT
WHO WRITES ABOUT ANGELS?

223
00:11:28,905 --> 00:11:31,691
WOW.

224
00:11:35,259 --> 00:11:37,000
SO, WHO ELSE?

225
00:11:37,044 --> 00:11:38,828
KATIE.

226
00:11:38,872 --> 00:11:40,569
MM-HMM.

227
00:11:40,612 --> 00:11:44,225
WHO YOU LET GO
TO A CONCERT TONIGHT...

228
00:11:44,268 --> 00:11:47,097
WITHOUT ASKING ME?

229
00:11:47,141 --> 00:11:49,317
IT'S NOT
THE DARK AGES, GEORGE.

230
00:11:49,360 --> 00:11:51,058
I DON'T HAVE TO ASK
YOUR PERMISSION.

231
00:11:51,101 --> 00:11:52,276
EXCUSE ME?

232
00:11:57,542 --> 00:11:59,936
WELL, WHEN IT COMES
TO OUR DAUGHTER,

233
00:11:59,980 --> 00:12:02,722
YOU DO, RIGHT?

234
00:12:05,246 --> 00:12:08,162
JUST GOT USED TO MAKING
DECISIONS ON MY OWN

235
00:12:08,205 --> 00:12:09,293
WHEN YOU WERE AWAY.

236
00:12:09,337 --> 00:12:10,991
[ LAUGHS ]

237
00:12:11,034 --> 00:12:14,472
WH... WHILE I WAS AWAY?
WHAT?

238
00:12:14,516 --> 00:12:16,779
NO, YOU THREW ME OUT.
REMEMBER?

239
00:12:16,823 --> 00:12:19,564
YOU THREW ME DOWN THE STAIRS
AND BROKE MY ARM.

240
00:12:22,132 --> 00:12:25,092
SO, WHAT, THIS IS HOW
YOU TALK TO ME NOW?

241
00:12:25,135 --> 00:12:29,183
WELL, AT LEAST
I DIDN'T PRESS CHARGES.

242
00:12:29,226 --> 00:12:31,011
YOU KNOW, YOU COULD
THANK ME FOR THAT.

243
00:12:34,144 --> 00:12:35,232
THANK YOU?

244
00:12:37,974 --> 00:12:40,803
[ Laughing ] WOW.

245
00:12:40,847 --> 00:12:43,980
SO, I GO AWAY FOR, WHAT,
FOUR MONTHS, I COME BACK,

246
00:12:44,024 --> 00:12:47,114
EVERYTHING HERE
IS DIFFERENT.

247
00:12:47,157 --> 00:12:50,378
YOU HAVE A NEW OUTFIT.

248
00:12:50,421 --> 00:12:53,294
YOU HAVE A NEW HAIRDO.

249
00:12:55,339 --> 00:12:56,558
YOU HAVE A NEW ATTITUDE.

250
00:12:56,601 --> 00:12:58,647
IS THERE ANYTHING ELSE?

251
00:13:00,910 --> 00:13:03,130
WHAT WERE YOU WEARING
AT THE BAPTISM?

252
00:13:06,263 --> 00:13:08,962
NEVER MIND. EAT.
I FORGOT THE SALAD.

253
00:13:09,005 --> 00:13:10,354
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

254
00:13:23,063 --> 00:13:24,194
[ EXHALES SHARPLY ]

255
00:13:24,238 --> 00:13:26,196
I SAID,
"WHAT WERE YOU WEARING"?

256
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:27,328
GEORGE, PLEASE...

257
00:13:30,374 --> 00:13:32,202
JUST TELL ME.

258
00:13:32,246 --> 00:13:34,596
[ SIGHS ]

259
00:13:36,641 --> 00:13:39,949
A LONG SHIRT
OVER A BATHING SUIT.

260
00:13:39,993 --> 00:13:42,517
SO YOU MADE A SPECTACLE
OF YOURSELF.

261
00:13:42,560 --> 00:13:44,736
IT WAS A SACRED CEREMONY.

262
00:13:44,780 --> 00:13:46,129
IN FRONT
OF THE ENTIRE TOWN.

263
00:13:46,173 --> 00:13:47,783
IT WAS NOT
THE ENTIRE TOWN.

264
00:13:47,827 --> 00:13:50,177
A WET SHIRT... EVERYONE SEE
HOW TURNED ON YOU WERE?

265
00:13:50,220 --> 00:13:52,005
I WASN'T TURNED ON, GEORGE.

266
00:13:52,048 --> 00:13:54,050
BY HIM, HUH?

267
00:13:56,313 --> 00:13:57,532
BY YOUR PASTOR.

268
00:13:57,575 --> 00:13:58,620
YOU'RE BEING RIDICULOUS.

269
00:14:01,144 --> 00:14:02,319
AAH!

270
00:14:02,363 --> 00:14:03,494
[ DISHES CLATTERING,
GLASS BREAKING ]

271
00:14:03,538 --> 00:14:04,931
OW. [ BREATHING HEAVILY ]
OKAY.

272
00:14:04,974 --> 00:14:06,454
YOU'RE NOT GOING
TO THAT CHURCH ANYMORE.

273
00:14:06,497 --> 00:14:07,629
[ GLASS BREAKING ]AAH!

274
00:14:07,672 --> 00:14:11,067
[ Crying ]
STOP IT, GEORGE.

275
00:14:11,111 --> 00:14:14,375
[ CRICKETS CHIRPING ]

276
00:14:20,598 --> 00:14:22,035
[ GUNSHOT ]

277
00:14:22,078 --> 00:14:23,079
[ DOG BARKING ]

278
00:14:24,472 --> 00:14:25,647
[ ENGINE TURNS OVER ]

279
00:14:25,690 --> 00:14:29,085
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

280
00:14:29,129 --> 00:14:30,913
Emmet:
PASTOR DREW, YOU'RE BACK.

281
00:14:30,957 --> 00:14:33,437
YEAH, I NEED TO PICK UP
A FEW THINGS FOR KATIE,

282
00:14:33,481 --> 00:14:36,223
AND I THOUGHT I'D CLEAN UP
IF YOU WERE GUYS ARE DONE.

283
00:14:36,266 --> 00:14:38,878
WELL, WE ALREADY ORDERED
A CLEAN-UP FOR TOMORROW.

284
00:14:38,921 --> 00:14:40,488
WELL, I'D LIKE TO GET
IN THERE IF I CAN.

285
00:14:40,531 --> 00:14:41,663
I'D HATE TO RISK KATIE
SEEING IT.

286
00:14:41,706 --> 00:14:43,056
UH...

287
00:14:43,099 --> 00:14:44,144
MY GUYS ARE DONE.

288
00:14:44,187 --> 00:14:45,928
OKAY?

289
00:14:45,972 --> 00:14:48,278
YEAH. IT IS PRETTY GRUESOME
IN THERE.

290
00:14:48,322 --> 00:14:49,714
THERE'S A LOT
OF BLOOD, PASTOR.

291
00:14:49,758 --> 00:14:52,456
I CAN HANDLE IT.

292
00:14:52,500 --> 00:14:54,676
[ Slowly ]
OKAY.

293
00:14:54,719 --> 00:14:56,243
I WISH SOMEBODY
WOULD CLEAN MY HOUSE.

294
00:14:59,594 --> 00:15:02,075
MRS. BENINCASA?

295
00:15:02,118 --> 00:15:04,033
YES?

296
00:15:04,077 --> 00:15:05,339
I'M HEATHER LaROCHE.

297
00:15:05,382 --> 00:15:07,732
I WAS A FRIEND
OF ALICE HAYWARD'S.

298
00:15:07,776 --> 00:15:09,473
AH.
I REALLY NEED
TO TALK TO YOU.

299
00:15:09,517 --> 00:15:11,258
COME IN. SIT DOWN.

300
00:15:11,301 --> 00:15:12,389
THANK YOU.

301
00:15:15,305 --> 00:15:16,567
[ SIGHS ]

302
00:15:16,611 --> 00:15:19,875
I JUST FEEL SO SICK
ABOUT THIS.

303
00:15:19,919 --> 00:15:23,792
JUST BEEN TRYING
TO MAKE SENSE OF IT.

304
00:15:23,835 --> 00:15:27,404
I WAS... I WAS HOPING
YOU COULD TELL ME SOMETHING.

305
00:15:27,448 --> 00:15:31,060
I'M SORRY. I CAN'T TALK
ABOUT IT AT THIS TIME.

306
00:15:31,104 --> 00:15:33,106
WERE YOU A FRIEND
OF GEORGE'S, AS WELL?

307
00:15:33,149 --> 00:15:34,803
NO, NO, JUST ALICE.

308
00:15:34,846 --> 00:15:38,763
IN FACT, WE ONLY BECAME FRIENDS
IN THE LAST FEW MONTHS,

309
00:15:38,807 --> 00:15:43,638
BUT I FELT LIKE WE'D KNOWN
EACH OTHER A LONG TIME.

310
00:15:43,681 --> 00:15:46,641
SHE, UM... [ CHUCKLES ]

311
00:15:46,684 --> 00:15:49,426
SHE CAME TO MY SHOP
ONE AFTERNOON.

312
00:15:52,516 --> 00:15:57,652
SHE APPEARED TO BE LOST,
LOOKING FOR SOMETHING...

313
00:15:57,695 --> 00:16:01,482
OR SOMEONE TO HELP HER.

314
00:16:01,525 --> 00:16:03,875
WHAT DO YOU MEAN?

315
00:16:03,919 --> 00:16:09,925
WELL, ALICE DIDN'T TALK MUCH
ABOUT HER PRIVATE LIFE.

316
00:16:09,969 --> 00:16:12,754
HER RELATIONSHIP WITH GEORGE
SEEMED OFF LIMITS.

317
00:16:12,797 --> 00:16:14,625
DID SHE SAY WHY?

318
00:16:14,669 --> 00:16:17,889
NO. WE... WHEN ALICE AND I

319
00:16:17,933 --> 00:16:19,369
WERE GETTING
TO KNOW EACH OTHER,

320
00:16:19,413 --> 00:16:20,675
IT WAS WHILE
THEY WERE SEPARATED.

321
00:16:20,718 --> 00:16:23,547
UM, THEY GOT BACK TOGETHER

322
00:16:23,591 --> 00:16:27,421
JUST... JUST
BEFORE HER BAPTISM.

323
00:16:27,464 --> 00:16:30,119
UH, WHEN WAS SHE BAPTIZED?

324
00:16:30,163 --> 00:16:32,382
YESTERDAY.

325
00:16:34,515 --> 00:16:37,779
SHE WAS SO HAPPY.

326
00:16:37,822 --> 00:16:40,260
DO YOU KNOW ANYONE ELSE
WHO COULD TELL US MORE

327
00:16:40,303 --> 00:16:43,132
ABOUT ALICE'S RELATIONSHIP
WITH GEORGE?

328
00:16:43,176 --> 00:16:45,787
GINNY McBRADDEN.

329
00:16:45,830 --> 00:16:48,311
THEY WERE BEST FRIENDS.

330
00:16:48,355 --> 00:16:50,270
WHY?

331
00:16:50,313 --> 00:16:53,708
'CAUSE HE BEAT THE CRAP
OUT OF HER FOR YEARS.

332
00:16:53,751 --> 00:16:56,145
HE WHIPPED HER LIKE A DOG.

333
00:16:56,189 --> 00:16:58,408
I HAD NO IDEA.

334
00:16:58,452 --> 00:17:01,498
NO ONE DID.

335
00:17:01,542 --> 00:17:04,762
SHE WAS EMBARRASSED BY IT,
ASHAMED.

336
00:17:04,806 --> 00:17:07,939
BUT EVENTUALLY SHE'D HAD
ENOUGH AND THREW HIM OUT?

337
00:17:07,983 --> 00:17:10,594
YEAH, AND THEN
AFTER A FEW MONTHS,

338
00:17:10,638 --> 00:17:13,293
SHE LET HIM COME BACK.

339
00:17:13,336 --> 00:17:15,251
AND YOU KNOW THE REST.

340
00:17:15,295 --> 00:17:16,644
[ CELLPHONE RINGING ]

341
00:17:16,687 --> 00:17:20,082
SORRY. JUST BE A MOMENT.

342
00:17:20,126 --> 00:17:22,563
I APPRECIATE YOU NOT BOTHERING
KATIE WITH ALL OF THIS.

343
00:17:22,606 --> 00:17:24,043
SHE'S BEEN THROUGH ENOUGH.

344
00:17:26,088 --> 00:17:29,657
DID, UH... DID GEORGE
EVER HIT KATIE?

345
00:17:29,700 --> 00:17:32,399
NO. HE LOVED THAT GIRL.

346
00:17:32,442 --> 00:17:33,487
AND SHE LOVED HIM.

347
00:17:33,530 --> 00:17:35,228
SHE WAS
HIS LITTLE PRINCESS.

348
00:17:35,271 --> 00:17:37,534
HE NEVER EVEN TOUCHED ALICE
WHEN SHE WAS AROUND.

349
00:17:37,578 --> 00:17:39,232
AND THEY CERTAINLY
SEEMED TO KNOW

350
00:17:39,275 --> 00:17:40,581
HOW TO KEEP UP APPEARANCES.

351
00:17:40,624 --> 00:17:43,801
YOU COULD SAY THAT.

352
00:17:43,845 --> 00:17:45,977
SHE DID CONFIDE IN YOU?
SURE.

353
00:17:46,021 --> 00:17:48,458
AND SHE TOLD YOU THE TRUTH
ABOUT HER MARRIAGE?

354
00:17:48,502 --> 00:17:50,373
SOME OF IT.

355
00:17:50,417 --> 00:17:53,637
BUT SHE KNEW I HAD ZERO SYMPATHY
FOR THAT MAN, NONE.

356
00:17:55,422 --> 00:17:58,903
I CHEERED
WHEN SHE KICKED HIM OUT.

357
00:17:58,947 --> 00:18:02,081
AND I CURSED WHEN
SHE BROUGHT HIM BACK,

358
00:18:02,124 --> 00:18:04,779
AT WHICH POINT SHE STOPPED
TALKING TO ME ABOUT IT.

359
00:18:04,822 --> 00:18:07,390
SO THIS WAS A WOMAN WHO HAD
NO ONE TO CONFIDE IN

360
00:18:07,434 --> 00:18:09,914
AND NOWHERE TO GO.

361
00:18:09,958 --> 00:18:13,831
OH, SHE HAD SOMEWHERE TO GO...
PASTORAL COUNSELING.

362
00:18:13,875 --> 00:18:15,529
WHAT DOES THAT MEAN?

363
00:18:15,572 --> 00:18:17,574
[ EMMET SPEAKING INDISTINCTLY ]

364
00:18:17,618 --> 00:18:19,359
ASK STEPHEN DREW.

365
00:18:19,402 --> 00:18:21,448
UM, COME ON.
WE GOT TO GO.

366
00:18:21,491 --> 00:18:23,145
OKAY.

367
00:18:23,189 --> 00:18:25,104
UH, THANK YOU VERY MUCH
FOR YOUR TIME.

368
00:18:29,064 --> 00:18:32,633
YEAH, OKAY,
WE'RE ON OUR WAY.

369
00:18:32,676 --> 00:18:35,418
WELL, THAT'S INTERESTING.

370
00:18:35,462 --> 00:18:37,333
WHAT'S GOING ON?

371
00:18:37,377 --> 00:18:38,595
THAT WAS
THE MEDICAL EXAMINER.

372
00:18:38,639 --> 00:18:40,771
GEORGE HAYWARD
DIDN'T SHOOT HIMSELF.

373
00:18:40,815 --> 00:18:42,512
SOMEONE ELSE DID.

374
00:18:55,046 --> 00:18:57,440
THE ENTRANCE WOUND

375
00:18:57,484 --> 00:18:59,050
HAS A DOWNWARD TRAJECTORY
OF A 90-DEGREE ANGLE.

376
00:18:59,094 --> 00:19:00,530
THE BLOOD SPATTER'S
INCONGRUENT

377
00:19:00,574 --> 00:19:02,532
WITH THE WOUND ENTERING
FROM ANY OTHER ANGLE.

378
00:19:02,576 --> 00:19:03,533
YEAH, BUT THE GUY WAS DRUNK.
THE GUN COULD HAVE SLIPPED.

379
00:19:03,577 --> 00:19:05,144
NOT ALL SUICIDES ARE TEXTBOOK.

380
00:19:05,187 --> 00:19:06,406
THERE WAS NO BLOWBACK
ON THE GUN.

381
00:19:06,449 --> 00:19:07,798
THERE WAS NO RESIDUE
ON HIS HAND.

382
00:19:07,842 --> 00:19:10,323
SO, DO YOU KNOW WHERE
THE SHOT CAME FROM?

383
00:19:10,366 --> 00:19:12,760
THE SHOT CAME IN HERE,
FROM BEHIND AND ABOVE.

384
00:19:12,803 --> 00:19:14,414
OKAY, SO,
THEY'RE HAVING DINNER,

385
00:19:14,457 --> 00:19:16,111
THEY HAVE A FIGHT,
IT ESCALATES,

386
00:19:16,155 --> 00:19:18,287
HE STRANGLES HER,
SOMEONE COMES IN TO STOP IT,

387
00:19:18,331 --> 00:19:19,767
IT'S TOO LATE,
AND THEN...

388
00:19:19,810 --> 00:19:22,422
EXCEPT SHE DIED FOUR HOURS
BEFORE HE DID.

389
00:19:22,465 --> 00:19:25,599
ALL RIGHT, SO, HE KILLS HER,

390
00:19:25,642 --> 00:19:26,730
THEN GETS LOADED
FOR A FEW HOURS...

391
00:19:26,774 --> 00:19:27,862
PASSES OUT.

392
00:19:27,905 --> 00:19:29,864
SOMEONE DISCOVERS THEM...

393
00:19:29,907 --> 00:19:32,649
...AND DECIDES TO EXACT
A LITTLE RETRIBUTION.

394
00:19:32,693 --> 00:19:34,390
WHOEVER DID IT

395
00:19:34,434 --> 00:19:35,391
WIPED THE GUN DOWN
AND PUT IT IN GEORGE'S HAND

396
00:19:35,435 --> 00:19:36,697
BEFORE TAKING OFF.

397
00:19:36,740 --> 00:19:38,394
IT ALL FITS.
YEP.

398
00:19:38,438 --> 00:19:40,091
COOL. UH,
ONE MORE THING...

399
00:19:40,135 --> 00:19:43,269
ALICE'S LOWER BACK WAS COVERED
WITH FRESH CONTUSIONS,

400
00:19:43,312 --> 00:19:44,748
24 TO 48 HOURS OLD.

401
00:19:44,792 --> 00:19:46,663
HER KIDNEYS
ARE BADLY BRUISED.

402
00:19:46,707 --> 00:19:49,753
SO, YOU'RE SAYING THAT
GEORGE BEAT HER A DAY OR TWO

403
00:19:49,797 --> 00:19:51,451
BEFORE HE KILLED HER?

404
00:19:51,494 --> 00:19:54,497
SON OF A BITCH.

405
00:19:59,328 --> 00:20:02,462
SO, MY DAD DIDN'T
KILL HIMSELF, THEN.

406
00:20:04,420 --> 00:20:06,335
SOMEONE SHOT HIM
WHEN HE WAS ASLEEP.

407
00:20:08,294 --> 00:20:10,121
KATIE, HE WAS UNCONSCIOUS
WHEN HE DIED.

408
00:20:10,165 --> 00:20:11,340
HE WOULDN'T HAVE FELT
A THING.

409
00:20:14,561 --> 00:20:19,043
SO, WHO WOULD WANT
TO KILL MY DAD, THEN?

410
00:20:19,087 --> 00:20:21,307
SOMEONE WHO WAS ANGRY
WITH HIM

411
00:20:21,350 --> 00:20:23,700
FOR WHAT HE DID
TO YOUR MOTHER.

412
00:20:23,744 --> 00:20:26,225
CAN YOU THINK
OF ANYBODY WHO...

413
00:20:28,357 --> 00:20:31,752
LIKE... LIKE A FRIEND
OR SOMETHING, LIKE...

414
00:20:31,795 --> 00:20:33,928
YEAH, SOMEONE WHO WAS CLOSE
TO YOUR MOM.

415
00:20:33,971 --> 00:20:36,713
MOM DIDN'T REALLY HAVE
A LOT OF CLOSE FRIENDS.

416
00:20:36,757 --> 00:20:38,759
NO ONE AT ALL?

417
00:20:38,802 --> 00:20:41,240
[ SIGHS HEAVILY ]

418
00:20:49,900 --> 00:20:52,251
THEY LOOK SO HAPPY HERE.

419
00:20:58,822 --> 00:21:02,783
[ SIGHS ]

420
00:21:02,826 --> 00:21:04,219
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

421
00:21:04,263 --> 00:21:05,786
YOU KNOW, I WISH
THAT SOMEBODY HAD A RECORDER

422
00:21:05,829 --> 00:21:08,615
AT MY MOM'S BAPTISM.

423
00:21:08,658 --> 00:21:12,445
SHE WAS SO HAPPY,
AND SHE WASN'T AFRAID ANYMORE.

424
00:21:12,488 --> 00:21:14,708
OF YOUR DAD?

425
00:21:14,751 --> 00:21:17,580
OR ELSE SHE WOULDN'T
HAVE DONE IT, YOU KNOW?

426
00:21:17,624 --> 00:21:18,581
DONE WHAT?

427
00:21:18,625 --> 00:21:19,887
GOT BAPTIZED.

428
00:21:19,930 --> 00:21:22,324
OH.

429
00:21:22,368 --> 00:21:25,632
SHE KNEW THAT HE'D GET MAD,
AND SHE JUST DIDN'T CARE.

430
00:21:25,675 --> 00:21:29,026
AND WHAT DID YOUR DAD THINK
OF STEPHEN DREW?

431
00:21:29,070 --> 00:21:32,073
OH, UH, HE HATED HIM.

432
00:21:38,253 --> 00:21:41,865
COME ON, GIRLS.
WE HAVE TO GO.

433
00:21:41,909 --> 00:21:43,693
KATIE.

434
00:21:43,737 --> 00:21:45,391
WHAT'S WRONG?

435
00:21:45,434 --> 00:21:48,394
I THINK SHE WANTS
TO BE LEFT ALONE.

436
00:21:50,831 --> 00:21:53,486
[ BELL CHIMES ]

437
00:21:53,529 --> 00:21:55,314
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

438
00:21:57,881 --> 00:22:00,797
Pastor Drew: HTH?

439
00:22:04,192 --> 00:22:09,284
HOW DO WE GATHER IN THE PLACE
WHERE SHE WORSHIPPED,

440
00:22:09,328 --> 00:22:14,245
SHE LOVED SO MUCH,
SHE DID SUCH GOOD WORK,

441
00:22:14,289 --> 00:22:17,597
AND NOT HAVE HER AMONG US?

442
00:22:20,295 --> 00:22:23,124
WELL, SHE IS WITH US.

443
00:22:23,167 --> 00:22:25,213
SHE'S ALL AROUND US.

444
00:22:25,256 --> 00:22:28,347
SHE'S IN OUR HEARTS...

445
00:22:28,390 --> 00:22:32,742
OUR MEMORY...

446
00:22:32,786 --> 00:22:34,309
GOOD WORK...

447
00:22:34,353 --> 00:22:38,400
AND... CERTAINLY IN HER BEAUTIFUL
DAUGHTER, KATIE.

448
00:22:42,099 --> 00:22:45,059
YOU KNOW, YOUR SMILE REMINDS ME
OF ONE OF YOUR MOTHER'S GIFTS.

449
00:22:45,102 --> 00:22:47,975
SHE COULD ALWAYS TAKE A NEGATIVE
AND TURN IT INTO A POSITIVE.

450
00:22:48,018 --> 00:22:52,414
YOU RECALL THE, UM... THE QUILT
THAT THE WOMEN'S CIRCLE MADE.

451
00:22:52,458 --> 00:22:55,025
TOOK THEM ABOUT A YEAR.
IT WAS A BEAUTIFUL QUILT.

452
00:22:55,069 --> 00:22:57,376
AND THEY WERE GONNA RAFFLE IT
OFF AT THE SUMMER FAIR.

453
00:22:57,419 --> 00:23:00,379
AND A FERAL CAT
FROM THE CEMETERY

454
00:23:00,422 --> 00:23:02,468
FOUND ITS WAY TO THAT QUILT,

455
00:23:02,511 --> 00:23:06,602
AND SHE GAVE BIRTH
TO A BEAUTIFUL LITTER.

456
00:23:06,646 --> 00:23:09,953
OF COURSE, THE QUILT WAS RUINED,
BUT ALICE JUST LOOKED AT IT

457
00:23:09,997 --> 00:23:13,435
AND SAID, "THANK GOD
THE KITTENS WERE WARM."

458
00:23:15,916 --> 00:23:17,918
"AND THANK GOD
THE KITTENS WERE SAFE."

459
00:23:21,574 --> 00:23:24,359
I COULD IMAGINE THERE WERE TIMES
IN ALICE'S LIFE

460
00:23:24,403 --> 00:23:26,013
WHERE SHE DIDN'T FEEL SAFE.

461
00:23:29,233 --> 00:23:31,366
BUT I'D LIKE TO BELIEVE
SHE'S SAFE NOW.

462
00:23:34,935 --> 00:23:37,546
YOU ARE WELCOME TO COME UP
AND PAY YOUR RESPECTS

463
00:23:37,590 --> 00:23:40,331
TO OUR BEAUTIFUL ALICE
AFTER THE FAMILY.

464
00:23:43,160 --> 00:23:45,946
[ INHALES SHARPLY ]

465
00:23:45,989 --> 00:23:48,122
HEY, MOM.

466
00:23:55,956 --> 00:23:58,001
I LOVE YOU.

467
00:24:03,224 --> 00:24:05,095
[ BREATHES DEEPLY ]

468
00:24:11,972 --> 00:24:13,843
Katie.

469
00:24:13,887 --> 00:24:16,106
HOW YOU HOLDING UP...
ALL RIGHT?

470
00:24:16,150 --> 00:24:17,804
YEAH. THANKS.

471
00:24:24,245 --> 00:24:27,814
HONEY, WHAT'S UP?

472
00:24:27,857 --> 00:24:31,034
HE'S HIDING SOMETHING.

473
00:24:34,385 --> 00:24:36,562
[ HORN HONKS ]

474
00:24:36,605 --> 00:24:38,346
THANK YOU, VICKY.[ KEYPAD BEEPS ]

475
00:24:38,389 --> 00:24:39,521
PASTOR. EXCUSE ME.

476
00:24:39,565 --> 00:24:41,305
[ CASH REGISTER DINGS ]

477
00:24:41,349 --> 00:24:43,873
WOULD YOU HAVE A MINUTE
TO TALK ABOUT ALICE HAYWARD?

478
00:24:43,917 --> 00:24:45,527
YOU KNOW,
IT'S BEEN A LONG DAY.

479
00:24:45,571 --> 00:24:48,312
I HOPE YOU UNDERSTAND.
I DO.

480
00:24:48,356 --> 00:24:50,967
I'LL JUST WALK WITH YOU,
IF YOU DON'T MIND.

481
00:24:51,011 --> 00:24:54,318
GINNY McBRADDEN SAID
THAT YOU COUNSELED ALICE,

482
00:24:54,362 --> 00:24:56,973
SO I THOUGHT YOU MIGHT BE ABLE
TO PROVIDE SOME INSIGHT.

483
00:24:57,017 --> 00:24:59,846
I'M SORRY.

484
00:24:59,889 --> 00:25:02,544
YOU WERE AWARE THAT ALICE

485
00:25:02,588 --> 00:25:06,156
WAS BEING ABUSED
BY GEORGE, CORRECT?

486
00:25:06,200 --> 00:25:08,550
I COUNSELED HER MANY TIMES
ABOUT HER MARRIAGE.

487
00:25:08,594 --> 00:25:10,465
THAT'S ALL I CAN SAY.

488
00:25:10,509 --> 00:25:12,946
DID YOU EVER DO ANYTHING
TO INTERVENE?

489
00:25:12,989 --> 00:25:15,557
NO.

490
00:25:18,342 --> 00:25:21,781
WAS ALICE SEEING ANYBODY ELSE
WHILE SHE WAS SEPARATED?

491
00:25:21,824 --> 00:25:24,479
I'LL REMIND YOU
ALICE WAS BURIED TODAY.

492
00:25:24,523 --> 00:25:26,307
PLEASE SHOW
A LITTLE RESPECT.

493
00:25:26,350 --> 00:25:28,004
AND I'LL REMIND YOU

494
00:25:28,048 --> 00:25:29,615
THAT WE ARE JUST CONDUCTING
AN INVESTIGATION.

495
00:25:29,658 --> 00:25:33,532
NOW, SOMEBODY SHOT GEORGE
AFTER GEORGE KILLED ALICE,

496
00:25:33,575 --> 00:25:35,621
SO MAYBE SHE MENTIONED
ANOTHER MAN

497
00:25:35,664 --> 00:25:37,057
DURING HER COUNSELING
WITH YOU.

498
00:25:37,100 --> 00:25:38,580
MAYBE HE KNEW SOMETHING
ABOUT IT.

499
00:25:38,624 --> 00:25:40,582
CATHERINE,
I CAN'T SPEAK TO THAT.

500
00:25:40,626 --> 00:25:42,323
ALL RIGHT.
EARLIER LAST YEAR,

501
00:25:42,366 --> 00:25:44,281
ALICE KICKED GEORGE
OUT OF THE HOUSE,

502
00:25:44,325 --> 00:25:45,761
AND THEN SHE TOOK HIM BACK.

503
00:25:45,805 --> 00:25:48,677
BOY, YOU KEEP GOING, HUH? CAN YOU SPEAK TO THAT?

504
00:25:48,721 --> 00:25:50,549
THERE'S NO NEED
TO PATRONIZE ME.

505
00:25:50,592 --> 00:25:52,507
BUT HOW DID YOU FEEL
ABOUT THAT,

506
00:25:52,551 --> 00:25:55,554
AFTER ALICE FINALLY GOT
THE COURAGE TO KICK GEORGE OUT

507
00:25:55,597 --> 00:25:57,904
AND THEN SHE TURNED AROUND
AND TOOK HIM BACK?

508
00:25:57,947 --> 00:25:59,470
THAT MUST HAVE UPSET YOU.

509
00:25:59,514 --> 00:26:01,342
GEORGE WAS A DANGEROUS MAN,

510
00:26:01,385 --> 00:26:03,692
AND I TOLD HER THAT
MANY TIMES.

511
00:26:03,736 --> 00:26:06,521
CATHERINE,
THIS IS A TERRIBLE TRAGEDY.

512
00:26:06,565 --> 00:26:09,350
OTHER THAN THAT,
THAT'S ALL I CAN TELL YOU.

513
00:26:32,591 --> 00:26:35,506
ALICE'S SPIRIT
HAS NOW BEEN RELEASED.

514
00:26:39,032 --> 00:26:45,516
SHE'S NOW ONE WITH THE LIGHT,
WITH THE AIR... AND THE SKY.

515
00:26:46,909 --> 00:26:50,304
SHE HAS ENTERED
THE REALM OF ANGELS,

516
00:26:50,347 --> 00:26:52,045
AND THEY HAVE WELCOMED HER.

517
00:26:54,874 --> 00:26:59,835
LET THE GOODNESS OF ALICE'S
HEART EXPAND OUR HEARTS.

518
00:26:59,879 --> 00:27:06,842
LET ALICE AND THE ANGELS
COME TO US, INSPIRE US,

519
00:27:06,886 --> 00:27:10,977
REMIND US THAT THERE IS LIFE
IN THE AIR WE BREATHE...

520
00:27:11,020 --> 00:27:13,370
[ WIND CHIMES TINKLING ]

521
00:27:13,414 --> 00:27:15,242
...LIFE IN THE LIGHT WE SEEK.

522
00:27:19,768 --> 00:27:21,770
LET'S TAKE A MOMENT
TO CLOSE OUR EYES

523
00:27:21,814 --> 00:27:24,077
AND FEEL ALICE'S ENERGY
SURROUND US.

524
00:27:36,350 --> 00:27:38,134
[ LAUGHS ]

525
00:27:38,178 --> 00:27:39,266
HI, THERE.
HI.

526
00:27:39,309 --> 00:27:40,920
CAN I HELP YOU?

527
00:27:40,963 --> 00:27:43,662
I, UH... I WALK
BY YOUR STORE ALL THE TIME.

528
00:27:43,705 --> 00:27:45,402
I'VE... I'VE NEVER HAD
THE NERVE TO COME IN BEFORE.

529
00:27:45,446 --> 00:27:47,143
WELL, YOU'RE HERE NOW.
COME ON IN.

530
00:27:47,187 --> 00:27:49,319
GREAT.
TAKE A LOOK AROUND.

531
00:27:49,363 --> 00:27:50,364
I'M HEATHER.

532
00:27:50,407 --> 00:27:52,366
YEAH, I KNOW.
WE ALL KNOW.

533
00:27:52,409 --> 00:27:53,236
[ DOOR CLOSES, BELLS RING ]

534
00:27:53,280 --> 00:27:54,585
I'VE READ ALL YOUR BOOKS

535
00:27:54,629 --> 00:27:57,371
AND I'VE SEEN
YOUR INTERVIEWS ON TV

536
00:27:57,414 --> 00:28:00,940
AND ONCE I EVEN... I WROTE
HOW MUCH I LIKED YOUR WORK

537
00:28:00,983 --> 00:28:03,333
ON ONE OF THOSE
ONLINE BOOKSTORES.

538
00:28:03,377 --> 00:28:04,987
OH. THANKS FOR DOING THAT.

539
00:28:05,031 --> 00:28:07,424
I DON'T... I STOPPED
READING THOSE AWHILE AGO.

540
00:28:07,468 --> 00:28:09,252
SOME PEOPLE CAN BE
KIND OF NASTY.

541
00:28:09,296 --> 00:28:12,255
I PROMISE YOU, YOUR BOOKS
HAVE HELPED SO MANY PEOPLE.

542
00:28:15,345 --> 00:28:18,131
IT'S SO BEAUTIFUL IN HERE.

543
00:28:18,174 --> 00:28:20,002
IT'S SO PEACEFUL.

544
00:28:20,046 --> 00:28:22,613
THANK YOU.

545
00:28:22,657 --> 00:28:24,180
I'M SORRY.
I DIDN'T CATCH YOUR NAME.

546
00:28:24,224 --> 00:28:26,356
OH, MY GOD... ALICE,
ALICE HAYWARD.

547
00:28:26,400 --> 00:28:28,271
IT'S SO NICE TO MEET YOU.

548
00:28:28,315 --> 00:28:30,012
HI. IT'S NICE TO MEET YOU,
ALICE.

549
00:28:30,056 --> 00:28:31,100
IT WAS GREAT.

550
00:28:31,144 --> 00:28:33,059
WE TALKED ABOUT SPIRITUALITY

551
00:28:33,102 --> 00:28:35,496
AND ABOUT A LOT
OF DIFFERENT THINGS.

552
00:28:35,539 --> 00:28:37,411
YOU SHOULD READ THE BOOK.

553
00:28:37,454 --> 00:28:39,805
SHE TALKS ABOUT CHRIST
AS A PROPHET,

554
00:28:39,848 --> 00:28:42,546
LIKE BUDDHA OR KRISHNA.

555
00:28:42,590 --> 00:28:45,985
SHE SAYS THAT WE'RE ALL ONE,
ALL A PART OF THE UNIVERSE.

556
00:28:46,028 --> 00:28:48,509
HMM. I DON'T CARE
WHAT THE HELL SHE SAID,

557
00:28:48,552 --> 00:28:51,338
AS LONG AS IT INSPIRED YOU
TO KICK GEORGE OUT.

558
00:28:51,381 --> 00:28:53,296
I STILL THINK YOU SHOULD
GET A RESTRAINING ORDER.

559
00:28:53,340 --> 00:28:55,255
I DON'T NEED TO.

560
00:28:55,298 --> 00:28:58,345
ALICE,
HE'S NOT GONNA CHANGE.

561
00:28:58,388 --> 00:29:00,956
YOU NEED TO START
PROTECTING YOURSELF.

562
00:29:01,000 --> 00:29:03,742
GINNY, HE KNOWS
HE WENT TOO FAR.

563
00:29:03,785 --> 00:29:06,005
HE DOES.
THAT'S WHY HE'S STAYING AWAY.

564
00:29:06,048 --> 00:29:08,834
WHAT IF HE COMES BACK?
IT HASN'T BEEN THAT LONG.

565
00:29:11,053 --> 00:29:13,534
I DON'T WANT
TO PRESS CHARGES.

566
00:29:13,577 --> 00:29:14,927
I DON'T WANT PEOPLE
KNOWING.

567
00:29:14,970 --> 00:29:16,145
OH, PEOPLE KNOW.

568
00:29:16,189 --> 00:29:17,364
GINNY, PLEASE.

569
00:29:19,235 --> 00:29:22,891
NOT FOR MY SAKE,
BUT FOR KATIE'S, OKAY?

570
00:29:27,940 --> 00:29:29,202
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

571
00:29:29,245 --> 00:29:32,074
THANK YOU
FOR THE PRAYER CIRCLE.

572
00:29:32,118 --> 00:29:34,337
I CAN SEE
WHY ALICE LOVED IT.

573
00:29:34,381 --> 00:29:37,384
WELL, I'M JUST SORRY KATIE
WASN'T ABLE TO MAKE IT.

574
00:29:37,427 --> 00:29:38,907
I ENCOURAGED HER TO COME,

575
00:29:38,951 --> 00:29:40,474
BUT IT'S JUST
TOO SOON FOR HER.

576
00:29:40,517 --> 00:29:42,345
YEAH.

577
00:29:42,389 --> 00:29:45,218
HOW'S SHE DOING, ANYWAY?

578
00:29:45,261 --> 00:29:47,046
WELL, SHE'S A STRONG KID,

579
00:29:47,089 --> 00:29:49,570
BUT SHE'S... SHE'S
REALLY SUFFERING.

580
00:29:49,613 --> 00:29:51,398
SHE WON'T COME OUT
OF HER ROOM.

581
00:29:51,441 --> 00:29:53,661
I-I... I JUST DON'T KNOW
WHAT TO DO FOR HER.

582
00:29:53,704 --> 00:29:58,057
I CAN'T IMAGINE HOW DIFFICULT
THIS MUST BE FOR HER.

583
00:29:58,100 --> 00:30:00,581
PLEASE TELL HER
TO COME BY ANYTIME.

584
00:30:00,624 --> 00:30:04,237
YOU KNOW, YOU AND ALICE
REALLY CONNECTED.

585
00:30:04,280 --> 00:30:06,543
WHY DON'T YOU COME SEE HER?

586
00:30:06,587 --> 00:30:09,198
WELL, I DON'T WANT TO IMPOSE
IF SHE'D RATHER BE ALONE.

587
00:30:09,242 --> 00:30:10,896
SHE WON'T TALK TO ANYONE.

588
00:30:10,939 --> 00:30:13,463
I CAN'T SEEM TO GET
THROUGH TO HER.

589
00:30:13,507 --> 00:30:16,292
MAYBE SHE'LL TALK WITH YOU.

590
00:30:16,336 --> 00:30:18,294
I DON'T KNOW. THERE'S
SOMETHING ABOUT THIS PASTOR.

591
00:30:18,338 --> 00:30:19,730
I DON'T TRUST HIM.

592
00:30:19,774 --> 00:30:21,558
HE'S EDGY WITH ME.
HE'S DEFENSIVE.

593
00:30:21,602 --> 00:30:22,777
WHAT ABOUT
THE BEST FRIEND?

594
00:30:22,821 --> 00:30:23,952
WOULDN'T SHE HAVE
JUST AS MUCH MOTIVE?

595
00:30:23,996 --> 00:30:25,867
WELL, SHE DOES
COME RIGHT OUT

596
00:30:25,911 --> 00:30:28,043
AND SAY HOW MUCH
SHE HATED GEORGE,

597
00:30:28,087 --> 00:30:32,004
BUT THE KIDS WERE BEST FRIENDS,
AND SHE ADORES KATIE.

598
00:30:32,047 --> 00:30:36,747
SO, NO MATTER HOW MUCH
SHE MAY HAVE DESPISED GEORGE,

599
00:30:36,791 --> 00:30:38,271
I DON'T SEE HER DOING THAT
TO KATIE.

600
00:30:38,314 --> 00:30:41,187
MY GUT SAYS STEPHEN DREW.

601
00:30:41,230 --> 00:30:43,319
WELL, DON'T LET YOUR GUT
INTERFERE WITH BUILDING A CASE.

602
00:30:43,363 --> 00:30:45,887
FOCUS ON THE LAW.
WE DON'T WANT A WITCH HUNT.

603
00:30:45,931 --> 00:30:49,151
OH, I FORGOT...
IT'S AN ELECTION YEAR.

604
00:30:49,195 --> 00:30:51,284
YOU'RE JUST WORRIED HOW
IT'LL LOOK TO THE VOTERS.

605
00:30:53,939 --> 00:30:55,331
YOU KNOW, NO ONE ELSE

606
00:30:55,375 --> 00:30:56,855
COULD GET AWAY
WITH SAYING THAT TO ME.

607
00:30:56,898 --> 00:30:59,770
AW, COME ON, JIM.
THAT'S WHY YOU HIRED ME.

608
00:30:59,814 --> 00:31:02,208
CATHERINE,
I'M SERIOUS ABOUT THIS.

609
00:31:02,251 --> 00:31:04,036
SO AM I, JIM.

610
00:31:04,079 --> 00:31:05,341
LOOK... WE ALL KNOW

611
00:31:05,385 --> 00:31:07,691
THAT GEORGE HAYWARD
WAS AN AWFUL MAN.

612
00:31:07,735 --> 00:31:10,390
HE BEAT HIS WIFE, AND THEN HE
KILLED HER, FOR GOD'S SAKE.

613
00:31:10,433 --> 00:31:11,957
BUT HE WAS PASSED OUT

614
00:31:12,000 --> 00:31:14,611
WHEN SOMEONE PUT A BULLET
THROUGH HIS HEAD,

615
00:31:14,655 --> 00:31:18,006
AND I DON'T CARE IF IT WAS
THE COUNTRY PASTOR WHO DID IT.

616
00:31:18,050 --> 00:31:21,270
I CARE THAT SOMEONE
DID IT.

617
00:31:21,314 --> 00:31:22,489
MURDER IS MURDER.

618
00:31:25,013 --> 00:31:27,015
THAT'S WHY I HIRED YOU.

619
00:31:33,239 --> 00:31:37,330
MY MOM WAS CHANGING,
WASN'T SHE?

620
00:31:37,373 --> 00:31:41,247
SHE WAS BECOMING
REALLY INDEPENDENT.

621
00:31:41,290 --> 00:31:43,640
BUT I THINK
THAT'S WHAT PUSHED HER

622
00:31:43,684 --> 00:31:46,295
AWAY FROM MY DAD.

623
00:31:46,339 --> 00:31:49,951
I THINK SO, YEAH.

624
00:31:49,995 --> 00:31:52,475
BUT THEN
SHE GOT TO DISCOVER

625
00:31:52,519 --> 00:31:55,217
SOME OF THE ANGELS
IN HER LIFE.

626
00:31:55,261 --> 00:31:57,089
I THINK THAT'S WHY
SHE HUNG OUT WITH YOU

627
00:31:57,132 --> 00:31:58,046
AND PASTOR DREW SO MUCH.

628
00:31:58,090 --> 00:32:00,919
[ CHUCKLES ]

629
00:32:00,962 --> 00:32:04,618
WELL, IF YOU'RE SUGGESTING
WE WERE HER ANGELS,

630
00:32:04,661 --> 00:32:07,926
I'M AFRAID WE DIDN'T DO
A VERY GOOD JOB.

631
00:32:07,969 --> 00:32:11,451
WELL, I'M GLAD THAT
SHE HAD YOU GUYS, ANYWAY.

632
00:32:11,494 --> 00:32:12,931
ME, TOO.

633
00:32:16,282 --> 00:32:19,589
WHAT IS IT?

634
00:32:19,633 --> 00:32:22,201
YOU KNOW THAT THING YOU GAVE
MY MOM AT THE PICNIC?

635
00:32:22,244 --> 00:32:23,332
YEAH. THE GANESH?

636
00:32:23,376 --> 00:32:25,378
YEAH.
I WAS TALKING TO GINNY,

637
00:32:25,421 --> 00:32:28,163
AND I SAID THAT IT SHOULD GO
IN HER CASKET.

638
00:32:28,207 --> 00:32:30,992
I THINK SHE REALLY
WOULD HAVE LIKED IT THERE.

639
00:32:31,036 --> 00:32:34,256
BUT THE THING IS [SIGHS]

640
00:32:34,300 --> 00:32:37,520
PASTOR DREW WANTED HER
TO HAVE HIS BIBLE.

641
00:32:37,564 --> 00:32:39,261
LIKE, HIS PERSONAL BIBLE?

642
00:32:39,305 --> 00:32:41,046
YEAH.

643
00:32:41,089 --> 00:32:42,612
WOW.

644
00:32:44,788 --> 00:32:47,966
I DIDN'T WANT MY MOM
TO LIE THERE FOREVER

645
00:32:48,009 --> 00:32:51,578
WITH A BIBLE IN HER HANDS,
EVEN IF IT WAS HIS.

646
00:32:51,621 --> 00:32:54,189
DOES HE KNOW THAT?

647
00:32:54,233 --> 00:32:55,974
OH, NO.
CAN WE NOT TELL HIM?

648
00:32:56,017 --> 00:32:57,105
'CAUSE, I MEAN, HE THINKS
IT'S WITH HER AND...

649
00:32:57,149 --> 00:32:58,672
I WOULDN'T TELL HIM.

650
00:32:58,715 --> 00:33:00,065
THANKS.

651
00:33:10,379 --> 00:33:12,207
[ WIND CHIMES TINKLING ]

652
00:33:16,081 --> 00:33:18,387
[ BELLS RING ]

653
00:33:18,431 --> 00:33:21,260
[ CHILDREN
SHOUTING INDISTINCTLY ]

654
00:33:26,482 --> 00:33:28,615
PASTOR.

655
00:33:28,658 --> 00:33:33,750
SO TRANQUIL HERE, SO SAFE.

656
00:33:33,794 --> 00:33:35,491
NO WONDER ALICE LIKED IT.

657
00:33:35,535 --> 00:33:37,580
[ CHUCKLES ]

658
00:33:37,624 --> 00:33:39,669
STEPHEN DREW IN MY SHOP.

659
00:33:39,713 --> 00:33:42,629
HMM. WELL, I WANTED TO COME

660
00:33:42,672 --> 00:33:46,198
AND, WELL, JUST BE
AROUND PEOPLE THAT SHE KNEW,

661
00:33:46,241 --> 00:33:47,677
PEOPLE THAT SHE LIKED.

662
00:33:47,721 --> 00:33:49,723
WELL, GINNY AND ALICE
WERE MUCH CLOSER.

663
00:33:49,766 --> 00:33:52,769
YEAH, BUT ALICE
WAS INSPIRED BY YOU.

664
00:33:55,511 --> 00:33:58,253
I MEAN, SHE SEEMED TO SEE
A CONNECTION

665
00:33:58,297 --> 00:33:59,733
BETWEEN OUR BELIEFS.

666
00:33:59,776 --> 00:34:02,866
I'M TRYING TO FIGURE OUT
WHAT THAT IS.

667
00:34:02,910 --> 00:34:07,262
WELL, THEY'RE NOT
SO DIFFERENT.

668
00:34:07,306 --> 00:34:10,309
I COULD START WITH ANGELS.

669
00:34:10,352 --> 00:34:12,311
I THINK YOU AND I
PROBABLY VIEW THEM

670
00:34:12,354 --> 00:34:14,878
IN MUCH THE SAME WAY...

671
00:34:14,922 --> 00:34:17,533
CELESTIAL GUIDES
AND PROTECTORS.

672
00:34:17,577 --> 00:34:19,144
[ CHUCKLES ]

673
00:34:19,187 --> 00:34:20,710
WHERE WERE
ALICE'S ANGELS?

674
00:34:20,754 --> 00:34:24,845
I DON'T KNOW.

675
00:34:24,888 --> 00:34:26,629
I WISH I COULD HAVE
DONE MORE FOR HER.

676
00:34:26,673 --> 00:34:30,459
MM. ME, TOO.

677
00:34:30,503 --> 00:34:33,375
[ HORN HONKS ]

678
00:34:33,419 --> 00:34:35,377
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

679
00:34:37,423 --> 00:34:38,641
GINNY, EXCUSE ME.

680
00:34:38,685 --> 00:34:40,295
I HAVE SOME MORE QUESTIONS
FOR YOU

681
00:34:40,339 --> 00:34:41,775
ABOUT THE NIGHT
OF THE MURDERS.

682
00:34:41,818 --> 00:34:43,472
FOR ME?
MM-HMM.

683
00:34:43,516 --> 00:34:45,213
[ SCOFFS ]

684
00:34:45,257 --> 00:34:47,650
WELL, THE PERSON
YOU SHOULD BE SPEAKING TO

685
00:34:47,694 --> 00:34:48,956
IS DOWN AT AURASCAPES,

686
00:34:48,999 --> 00:34:51,306
PAYING A VISIT
TO HEATHER LaROCHE.

687
00:34:51,350 --> 00:34:53,613
HEATHER LaROCHE?

688
00:34:53,656 --> 00:34:55,441
I HONORED STEPHEN'S REQUEST
TO PROTECT KATIE,

689
00:34:55,484 --> 00:34:57,356
BUT I CANNOT GET PAST HIM
FLIRTING WITH HEATHER

690
00:34:57,399 --> 00:34:58,792
ON TOP OF EVERYTHING ELSE.

691
00:34:58,835 --> 00:35:01,403
ALL RIGHT, NOTED, BUT I NEED
TO KNOW WHERE YOU WERE

692
00:35:01,447 --> 00:35:02,883
WHEN GEORGE HAYWARD
WAS KILLED.

693
00:35:02,926 --> 00:35:05,146
IN MY BED, ASLEEP.

694
00:35:05,190 --> 00:35:07,670
CAN ANYONE VERIFY THAT?

695
00:35:07,714 --> 00:35:09,803
WHAT'S THIS ABOUT?

696
00:35:09,846 --> 00:35:11,674
GINNY...

697
00:35:11,718 --> 00:35:13,763
DID ALICE WRITE SOMETHING
ABOUT ME IN HER JOURNAL?

698
00:35:13,807 --> 00:35:15,678
EXCUSE ME?

699
00:35:15,722 --> 00:35:17,376
YOU HAVEN'T FOUND
ALICE'S JOURNAL?

700
00:35:17,419 --> 00:35:20,118
IT'S IN HER HOUSE
SOMEWHERE,

701
00:35:20,161 --> 00:35:21,989
AND I'M SURE WHATEVER
SHE WROTE ABOUT ME

702
00:35:22,032 --> 00:35:24,209
IS MUCH LESS INTERESTING
THAN WHATEVER SHE WROTE
ABOUT THE AFFAIR.

703
00:35:24,252 --> 00:35:26,863
GEORGE WAS HAVING
AN AFFAIR?

704
00:35:26,907 --> 00:35:28,213
HELLO?

705
00:35:28,256 --> 00:35:30,432
ALICE WAS HAVING
AN AFFAIR?

706
00:35:30,476 --> 00:35:32,782
WITH WHO?

707
00:35:32,826 --> 00:35:35,655
TAKE A BIG GUESS.

708
00:35:43,576 --> 00:35:44,707
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

709
00:35:44,751 --> 00:35:46,144
[ INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS ]

710
00:35:51,497 --> 00:35:55,501
I'VE BEEN COMING TO YOUR CHURCH
FOR THREE YEARS,

711
00:35:55,544 --> 00:35:59,679
BUT I'VE NEVER REALLY KNOWN
ANYTHING ABOUT YOU

712
00:35:59,722 --> 00:36:01,855
UNTIL NOW.

713
00:36:01,898 --> 00:36:04,727
I DON'T UNDERSTAND.

714
00:36:04,771 --> 00:36:07,295
I'M SURE YOU DON'T.

715
00:36:07,339 --> 00:36:09,297
WHAT IS THAT?

716
00:36:09,341 --> 00:36:10,777
ALICE'S JOURNAL.

717
00:36:13,562 --> 00:36:18,219
SHE STARTED KEEPING IT RIGHT
AFTER SHE THREW GEORGE OUT.

718
00:36:18,263 --> 00:36:21,701
AND IT'S PRETTY CLEAR
THAT, DURING THAT TIME,

719
00:36:21,744 --> 00:36:23,137
PASTORAL COUNSELING

720
00:36:23,181 --> 00:36:25,618
WASN'T THE ONLY THING
SHE GOT FROM YOU.

721
00:36:27,663 --> 00:36:30,579
[ EXHALES HEAVILY ]

722
00:36:33,539 --> 00:36:36,019
IS THIS UNCOMFORTABLE
FOR YOU?

723
00:36:36,063 --> 00:36:39,284
I NEVER MEANT FOR THIS
TO HAPPEN.

724
00:36:39,327 --> 00:36:41,416
THAT'S THE TRUTH.
I SWEAR TO GOD.

725
00:37:08,226 --> 00:37:10,880
Alice: [ Voice breaking ]
I KICKED HIM OUT.

726
00:37:10,924 --> 00:37:13,927
BUT I'M SCARED.

727
00:37:13,970 --> 00:37:16,364
OF WHAT?

728
00:37:19,933 --> 00:37:22,501
WHETHER I MADE
THE RIGHT DECISION OR NOT.

729
00:37:24,938 --> 00:37:28,768
MONTHS GO BY,
AND GEORGE IS WONDERFUL.

730
00:37:28,811 --> 00:37:31,771
HE'S TENDER.

731
00:37:31,814 --> 00:37:33,903
LONG STRETCHES
WHERE EVERYTHING'S FINE.

732
00:37:33,947 --> 00:37:37,037
[ SNIFFLES ]

733
00:37:37,080 --> 00:37:39,779
IT COMES
IN PEAKS AND VALLEYS.

734
00:37:39,822 --> 00:37:43,913
HE GETS SO ANGRY.

735
00:37:43,957 --> 00:37:46,568
AND THEN HE CALMS.

736
00:37:48,918 --> 00:37:50,442
BUT HE TRICKS YOU
WITH THAT CALM.

737
00:37:52,835 --> 00:37:55,011
YOU THINK IT'S SAFE,

738
00:37:55,055 --> 00:38:01,235
AND THEN SUDDENLY,
JUST OUT OF NOWHERE, HE RAGES.

739
00:38:01,279 --> 00:38:04,543
I THINK
YOU'RE VERY COURAGEOUS.

740
00:38:06,980 --> 00:38:09,939
I CAN'T HAVE KATIE
THINKING THIS IS NORMAL.

741
00:38:09,983 --> 00:38:11,550
IT'S MY FAULT.

742
00:38:11,593 --> 00:38:14,683
NO.

743
00:38:14,727 --> 00:38:16,468
IT'S DAMAGED HER.

744
00:38:16,511 --> 00:38:18,383
THEY USED TO BE SO CLOSE,

745
00:38:18,426 --> 00:38:22,822
BUT LATELY I FEEL HER
PULLING AWAY.

746
00:38:22,865 --> 00:38:25,825
IT MUST CHIP AWAY
HER LOVE FOR HIM.

747
00:38:25,868 --> 00:38:28,480
I'M SURE IT DOES.

748
00:38:28,523 --> 00:38:30,090
I HATE MYSELF FOR THAT.

749
00:38:30,133 --> 00:38:31,700
NO.

750
00:38:31,744 --> 00:38:35,487
I WANT TO BE
A GOOD EXAMPLE FOR HER.

751
00:38:35,530 --> 00:38:37,576
I DON'T WANT HER
REPEATING MY MISTAKES.

752
00:38:37,619 --> 00:38:39,621
GOOD.

753
00:38:39,665 --> 00:38:41,710
YOU KNOW, UNDER HIS ANGER,
GEORGE... HE'S A GOOD MAN.

754
00:38:41,754 --> 00:38:43,843
ALICE.
NO, HE IS.

755
00:38:43,886 --> 00:38:46,976
I SEE IT IN HIS EYES
WHEN HE APOLOGIZES. HE JUST...

756
00:38:47,020 --> 00:38:49,414
[ CHUCKLES ]

757
00:38:49,457 --> 00:38:52,852
HE WRITES POETRY
ASKING FOR MY FORGIVENESS.

758
00:38:55,245 --> 00:38:58,336
HURTING ME
DOESN'T MAKE HIM FEEL GOOD.

759
00:38:58,379 --> 00:39:00,642
IT JUST MAKES HIM
HATE HIMSELF MORE.

760
00:39:00,686 --> 00:39:02,035
WELL,
I'M SURE HE FEELS THAT,

761
00:39:02,078 --> 00:39:04,516
BUT, ALICE, YOU HAVE
TO TAKE THIS OPPORTUNITY

762
00:39:04,559 --> 00:39:06,692
TO STAY STRONG
AND FOLLOW THROUGH.

763
00:39:06,735 --> 00:39:08,128
DON'T TAKE HIM BACK.

764
00:39:11,392 --> 00:39:13,699
I'M SORRY.
IT'S NOT MY PLACE
TO TELL YOU THAT.

765
00:39:13,742 --> 00:39:14,961
OF COURSE IT IS.

766
00:39:15,004 --> 00:39:18,225
I RESPECT YOUR OPINION.

767
00:39:18,268 --> 00:39:22,098
IT'S JUST NOT SO EASY.
I MEAN, HE'S MY HUSBAND.

768
00:39:22,142 --> 00:39:23,883
I MADE VOWS BEFORE GOD.

769
00:39:23,926 --> 00:39:26,146
GOD DOESN'T WANT YOU
IN AN ABUSIVE RELATIONSHIP,

770
00:39:26,189 --> 00:39:27,756
VOWS OR NO VOWS.

771
00:39:27,800 --> 00:39:30,672
I'M SO WEAK.

772
00:39:30,716 --> 00:39:32,457
NO, YOU'RE NOT WEAK.

773
00:39:32,500 --> 00:39:36,461
YOU ARE STRONG.
YOU ARE INCREDIBLY STRONG.

774
00:39:38,071 --> 00:39:39,899
THANK YOU.

775
00:39:42,380 --> 00:39:44,338
Ginny: HOW DOES
YOUR WRIST FEEL?

776
00:39:44,382 --> 00:39:47,080
STIFF, BUT AT LEAST
IT'S OFF, RIGHT?

777
00:39:47,123 --> 00:39:49,517
OH, SINGLE LIFE SUITS YOU.

778
00:39:49,561 --> 00:39:50,866
I'm not single.

779
00:39:50,910 --> 00:39:52,868
I'M SEPARATED.

780
00:39:52,912 --> 00:39:55,044
OKAY. WHATEVER YOU ARE,
YOU'RE LOOKING GREAT.

781
00:39:55,088 --> 00:39:56,916
I FEEL GREAT.

782
00:39:56,959 --> 00:39:59,092
IT'S SUCH A LUXURY,
NOT BEING AFRAID.

783
00:39:59,135 --> 00:40:01,050
YOU KNOW, PEOPLE TAKE
THIS SORT OF THING FOR GRANTED.

784
00:40:01,094 --> 00:40:03,226
I WANT TO CELEBRATE.
[ CHUCKLES ]

785
00:40:03,270 --> 00:40:05,011
I JUST DON'T WANT ANYTHING BAD
TO HAPPEN TO YOU.

786
00:40:05,054 --> 00:40:06,316
NOTHING'S GONNA HAPPEN.

787
00:40:06,360 --> 00:40:07,883
ALL THE BAD STUFF
IS BEHIND ME.

788
00:40:07,927 --> 00:40:08,928
I CAN FEEL IT.

789
00:40:08,971 --> 00:40:10,625
HAS HE CONTACTED YOU?

790
00:40:10,669 --> 00:40:14,237
NO. NO, HE'S BEING
VERY RESPECTFUL.

791
00:40:14,281 --> 00:40:17,980
LET'S HAVE A SUNDAE.
COME ON!

792
00:40:21,201 --> 00:40:23,246
HI, HONEY.
HOW WAS SCHOOL?

793
00:40:23,290 --> 00:40:24,726
SIT DOWN.
I GOT YOU A SNACK.

794
00:40:28,338 --> 00:40:31,777
WHAT'S WRONG?

795
00:40:31,820 --> 00:40:33,953
IS HE COMING BACK?

796
00:40:33,996 --> 00:40:36,869
YOU WANT HIM TO?

797
00:40:36,912 --> 00:40:39,611
YEAH.

798
00:40:39,654 --> 00:40:41,700
[ CHUCKLES ]

799
00:40:41,743 --> 00:40:43,049
HERE.
THANKS.

800
00:40:43,092 --> 00:40:44,964
IT'S SO NICE TO SEE YOU

801
00:40:45,007 --> 00:40:48,271
WITHOUT YOUR iPOD AND THOSE
THINGS IN YOUR EARS AND...

802
00:40:48,315 --> 00:40:49,664
HEADPHONES?

803
00:40:49,708 --> 00:40:50,926
[ Chuckling ]
YEAH.
YEAH.

804
00:40:50,970 --> 00:40:51,971
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

805
00:40:52,014 --> 00:40:53,451
THEY BLOCK US OUT.

806
00:40:57,846 --> 00:40:59,152
I'M SORRY.

807
00:40:59,195 --> 00:41:02,677
OH, HONEY, IT'S MY FAULT.

808
00:41:02,721 --> 00:41:05,724
MOM, IT'S NOT
YOUR FAULT, OKAY?

809
00:41:05,767 --> 00:41:08,683
OKAY.

810
00:41:08,727 --> 00:41:09,945
THINGS ARE GONNA BE
DIFFERENT FROM NOW ON, BABY.

811
00:41:09,989 --> 00:41:11,817
I PROMISE YOU.

812
00:41:11,860 --> 00:41:14,689
OKAY. [ CHUCKLES ]

813
00:41:16,822 --> 00:41:17,823
HI.
Alice: HI.

814
00:41:17,866 --> 00:41:19,041
HOW WAS THE BOOK SIGNING?

815
00:41:19,085 --> 00:41:20,956
GOT HER TO AUTOGRAPH IT
FOR YOU.

816
00:41:21,000 --> 00:41:22,436
"TO PASTOR DREW,

817
00:41:22,480 --> 00:41:24,656
"MAY YOUR AURA
FOREVER GLOW BRIGHTLY

818
00:41:24,699 --> 00:41:26,222
AND ILLUMINE THE SKY."

819
00:41:26,266 --> 00:41:27,833
"THE SKY."YES, YES, "THE SKY."

820
00:41:27,876 --> 00:41:29,138
THIS SKY? THE SKY OR...

821
00:41:29,182 --> 00:41:31,445
THIS SKY... DON'T DISMISS IT
OUT OF HAND.

822
00:41:31,489 --> 00:41:34,187
I READ IT, AND IT'S EXPANSIVE
AND THRILLING

823
00:41:34,230 --> 00:41:35,884
'CAUSE IT'S NOT PUNITIVE.

824
00:41:35,928 --> 00:41:38,017
YOU KNOW, IT'S NOT BASED
IN REDEMPTION OR GUILT.

825
00:41:38,060 --> 00:41:41,194
IT'S JUST ABOUT BEING PRESENT,
HERE AND NOW.
MM-HMM.

826
00:41:41,237 --> 00:41:43,762
OH... [ SCOFFS ]

827
00:41:43,805 --> 00:41:45,677
YOU SHOULDN'T DO THAT.
YOU DON'T EVEN KNOW HER.

828
00:41:45,720 --> 00:41:46,939
WANT SOME TEA?
YES, PLEASE.

829
00:41:46,982 --> 00:41:48,331
[ TEAKETTLE WHISTLING ]

830
00:41:48,375 --> 00:41:50,246
YOU KNOW I WANT
A SPIRITUAL CONNECTION,

831
00:41:50,290 --> 00:41:52,248
AND I'M JUST NOT
COMPLETELY FULFILLED

832
00:41:52,292 --> 00:41:53,989
BY THE CHRISTIAN TEACHINGS.

833
00:41:54,033 --> 00:41:55,338
WELL, YOU CAN'T LEAVE
THE CHURCH.

834
00:41:55,382 --> 00:41:56,209
I'D QUIT THE PARISH
IN TWO SECONDS.

835
00:41:56,252 --> 00:41:57,123
REALLY?
MM-HMM.

836
00:41:57,166 --> 00:41:58,428
YOU WOULD QUIT?

837
00:41:58,472 --> 00:41:59,908
BECAUSE I COULDN'T
BEAR THE FACT

838
00:41:59,952 --> 00:42:01,388
OF LOOKING OUT
OVER THAT PULPIT

839
00:42:01,431 --> 00:42:03,085
AND NOT SEEING YOUR FACE,
THAT'S WHY.

840
00:42:03,129 --> 00:42:04,565
[ CHUCKLES ]
WHERE WOULD YOU GO?

841
00:42:04,609 --> 00:42:06,785
I DON'T KNOW.
DESERTED ISLAND SOMEWHERE.

842
00:42:06,828 --> 00:42:08,134
MM-HMM.
TALK TO COCONUTS.

843
00:42:08,177 --> 00:42:09,178
I'LL PREACH TO COCONUTS.

844
00:42:09,222 --> 00:42:12,181
[ LAUGHS ]

845
00:42:12,225 --> 00:42:14,923
HOW'S KATIE DOING?
HOW'S SHE ADJUSTING?

846
00:42:14,967 --> 00:42:18,753
SHE'S HELD SO MUCH IN
FOR SO LONG.

847
00:42:18,797 --> 00:42:20,842
NOW WHEN I SEE HER,

848
00:42:20,886 --> 00:42:24,803
SHE'S LIKE A LITTLE FLOWER
JUST READY TO BLOSSOM.

849
00:42:24,846 --> 00:42:28,894
I COULD SAY THE SAME THING
ABOUT YOU.

850
00:42:28,937 --> 00:42:30,896
[ CHUCKLES ]

851
00:42:30,939 --> 00:42:32,288
ANYWAY...

852
00:42:36,902 --> 00:42:39,252
WE'RE DOING MOTHER
AND DAUGHTER THINGS TOGETHER

853
00:42:39,295 --> 00:42:41,384
FOR THE FIRST TIME
SINCE SHE WAS A LITTLE GIRL.

854
00:42:41,428 --> 00:42:43,386
THAT'S AMAZING.
[ CHUCKLES ]

855
00:42:43,430 --> 00:42:46,389
SOMETHING SO SMALL
CAN SEEM SO BIG.

856
00:42:46,433 --> 00:42:48,348
I'VE BEEN PRAYING FOR YOU
A LOT.

857
00:42:50,219 --> 00:42:53,222
GOD, IT JUST ALWAYS
MAKES ME WANT TO CRY,

858
00:42:53,266 --> 00:42:55,573
TALKING ABOUT IT.

859
00:42:59,359 --> 00:43:02,928
ALICE, I CAN'T SEE HOW ANYONE
WOULD WANT TO HURT YOU, EVER.

860
00:43:11,327 --> 00:43:13,547
I'M SO SORRY.
NO.

861
00:43:13,591 --> 00:43:15,288
OH, MY GOD,
I'M SO EMBARRASSED.

862
00:43:15,331 --> 00:43:17,638
IT'S OKAY. NO, IT'S OKAY.
I'M NOT GONNA LIE.

863
00:43:17,682 --> 00:43:21,642
IT'S... IT'S NOT LIKE
I'M NOT ATTRACTED TO YOU.

864
00:43:21,686 --> 00:43:23,035
LET'S JUST FORGET
THIS EVER HAPPENED.

865
00:43:23,078 --> 00:43:24,079
NO.

866
00:43:24,123 --> 00:43:25,385
MMM.

867
00:43:28,257 --> 00:43:31,783
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

868
00:43:31,826 --> 00:43:34,002
PLEASE REMIND ME WHO I AM.

869
00:43:37,179 --> 00:43:38,877
[ GASPING LIGHTLY ]

870
00:44:24,183 --> 00:44:26,576
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

871
00:44:26,620 --> 00:44:28,883
YOU SLEPT
WITH STEPHEN DREW?

872
00:44:28,927 --> 00:44:30,885
THERE IS A WOMAN
UNDER THESE FRUMPY CLOTHES.

873
00:44:30,929 --> 00:44:32,017
YEAH, YEAH, YEAH, YEAH.

874
00:44:32,060 --> 00:44:33,496
SO, UH, DETAILS?

875
00:44:33,540 --> 00:44:35,673
[ SIGHS ] AMAZING!

876
00:44:35,716 --> 00:44:39,415
HE WAS SO GENEROUS
AND SO PRESENT AND SO HOT.

877
00:44:39,459 --> 00:44:41,113
[ LAUGHS ]
I DON'T THINK

878
00:44:41,156 --> 00:44:43,550
I'LL EVER BE ABLE TO LOOK
AT HIM THE SAME WAY.

879
00:44:43,593 --> 00:44:46,161
[ Laughing ]
ME, EITHER.

880
00:44:46,205 --> 00:44:48,033
IT'S ABOUT TIME.

881
00:44:48,076 --> 00:44:50,165
OH, GOD, THANK YOU.

882
00:44:50,209 --> 00:44:54,082
YOU KNOW, I NEVER THOUGHT OF
MYSELF AS THE SORT OF WOMAN

883
00:44:54,126 --> 00:44:55,257
WHO GETS TO TAKE A LOVER.

884
00:44:55,301 --> 00:44:57,303
MMM.
[ CHUCKLES ]

885
00:44:57,346 --> 00:44:58,304
"TAKE A LOVER."

886
00:44:58,347 --> 00:44:59,435
I TOOK A LOVER.

887
00:44:59,479 --> 00:45:01,176
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

888
00:45:01,220 --> 00:45:02,090
AND IT WAS GOOD.

889
00:45:02,134 --> 00:45:04,136
[ LAUGHS ]

890
00:45:04,179 --> 00:45:07,574
Alice: IN MY LIFE, THINGS HAVE
BEEN SO MUCH BETTER.

891
00:45:07,617 --> 00:45:10,925
I'M ABLE TO LAUGH
AND PLAY WITH KATIE.

892
00:45:10,969 --> 00:45:13,362
WE'RE SPENDING
SO MUCH MORE TIME TOGETHER.

893
00:45:13,406 --> 00:45:14,973
♪ I'M JUST A HOLOGRAM

894
00:45:15,016 --> 00:45:18,411
♪ YOU CAN SEE,
BUT DON'T TOUCH ME, BABY ♪

895
00:45:18,454 --> 00:45:20,587
♪ OH, I BET YOU WANT ME

896
00:45:20,630 --> 00:45:24,591
♪ I'M IN A LOVE AFFAIR
WITHOUT A LOVE SONG ♪

897
00:45:24,634 --> 00:45:27,420
♪ I'M IN THE HABIT
OF HAVING WHAT I DON'T WANT ♪

898
00:45:27,463 --> 00:45:31,380
I NEVER REALIZED HOW MUCH I WAS MISSING, HOW MUCH I SHUT DOWN.

899
00:45:31,424 --> 00:45:34,079
NOW I'M BEGINNING TO FEEL
ALL THE JOY

900
00:45:34,122 --> 00:45:35,602
THAT COMES WITH BEING PART
OF MY DAUGHTER'S LIFE.

901
00:45:35,645 --> 00:45:39,258
♪ I'M IN A LOVE AFFAIR
WITHOUT A LOVE SONG ♪

902
00:45:39,301 --> 00:45:42,565
♪ I'M IN THE HABIT
OF HAVING WHAT I DON'T WANT ♪

903
00:45:42,609 --> 00:45:44,785
♪ I'M JUST A HOLOGRAM

904
00:45:44,829 --> 00:45:47,570
♪ YOU CAN SEE,
BUT DON'T TOUCH ME, BABY ♪

905
00:45:47,614 --> 00:45:51,226
♪ OH, I BET YOU WANT ME NOW

906
00:45:51,270 --> 00:45:56,362
♪ DON'T TOUCH ME, BABY,
I'M JUST A HOLOGRAM ♪

907
00:45:56,405 --> 00:45:59,452
I CAN'T BELIEVE YOU CAME
TO ONE OF MY GAMES.

908
00:45:59,495 --> 00:46:01,802
WHAT, YOU KIDDING ME?
I LOVE WATCHING YOU PLAY.

909
00:46:01,846 --> 00:46:04,587
YOU KNOW WHAT?
YOU ARE GETTING PRETTY GOOD
WITH THAT LEFT FOOT.

910
00:46:04,631 --> 00:46:06,851
WELL, I'VE BEEN WORKING
ON IT.
YEAH?

911
00:46:06,894 --> 00:46:08,243
SO, WHAT'S IN THE BAG?

912
00:46:08,287 --> 00:46:10,115
WHAT, THIS BAG?

913
00:46:10,158 --> 00:46:12,944
A LITTLE SOMETHING FOR YOU.

914
00:46:12,987 --> 00:46:15,337
HELP MAKE YOU PLAY BETTER.

915
00:46:15,381 --> 00:46:17,035
[ CHUCKLES ]

916
00:46:17,078 --> 00:46:18,297
[ Slowly ]
OKAY.

917
00:46:18,340 --> 00:46:20,342
[ CHUCKLES ]

918
00:46:23,650 --> 00:46:25,695
THESE ARE LIKE 200 BUCKS.

919
00:46:25,739 --> 00:46:28,089
ONLY THE BEST FOR MY BABY,
RIGHT?

920
00:46:28,133 --> 00:46:30,091
[ SQUEALS ]

921
00:46:30,135 --> 00:46:32,050
OH, THANK YOU!

922
00:46:32,093 --> 00:46:33,921
YOU'RE WELCOME.

923
00:46:33,965 --> 00:46:36,271
I MISS YOU, DAD.

924
00:46:36,315 --> 00:46:39,187
I MISS YOU, TOO.

925
00:46:39,231 --> 00:46:40,406
INVITE ME
TO YOUR NEXT GAME?

926
00:46:40,449 --> 00:46:41,450
NOPE.

927
00:46:41,494 --> 00:46:43,496
[ DREW HUMMING ]

928
00:46:47,195 --> 00:46:49,110
HEY.

929
00:46:49,154 --> 00:46:52,113
HEY, PASTOR DREW.

930
00:46:52,157 --> 00:46:54,333
WHAT YOU DOING?

931
00:46:54,376 --> 00:46:57,727
WORKING ON YOUR MOM'S CAR,
YOU KNOW, DOING MANLY STUFF.

932
00:46:57,771 --> 00:47:00,295
[ DOOR OPENS ]Alice: STEPHEN?

933
00:47:00,339 --> 00:47:01,557
TIME FOR A BREAK.

934
00:47:01,601 --> 00:47:03,298
HEY, BABE.
HOW WAS SOCCER?

935
00:47:03,342 --> 00:47:04,299
GOOD.

936
00:47:04,343 --> 00:47:05,910
ICED TEA?

937
00:47:05,953 --> 00:47:08,651
UM, I'LL... I'LL BE FINE.
THANKS, THOUGH.

